      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="393-27L7" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">The inclosed <hi rend="underline">Simile</hi> I this instant received by the Post.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">B</hi>Ehold these <hi rend="underline">Monarch</hi> O<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">AKS</hi>, that rise</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-2"> With lofty <hi rend="underline">Branches</hi> to the Skies,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-3"> Have huge proportioned <hi rend="underline">Roots</hi>, that grow</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-4"> In equal <hi rend="underline">Longitude</hi> below:<gap/><gap/><hi rend="underline">Two</hi> B<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">ARDS</hi> that now in <hi rend="underline">Fashion</hi> reign,</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-5"> Most aptly this <hi rend="underline">Device</hi> explain;</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-6"> If <hi rend="underline">this</hi> on <hi rend="underline">Clouds</hi> and <hi rend="underline">Stars</hi> will venture,<hi rend="underline">That</hi> will creep downwards to the <hi rend="underline">Center</hi>.</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-7"> Or more to shew the Thing I mean,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-8"> Have we not o'er a S<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">AWPIT</hi> seen</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-9"> A skill'd <hi rend="underline">Mechanick</hi>, that has stood</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-10"> On a strong Plank of stubborn Wood,</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-11"> Who hir'd a <hi rend="underline">subterraneous</hi> Friend</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-12"> To take his <hi rend="underline">Iron</hi> by the <hi rend="underline">End</hi>;</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-13"> Yet which <hi rend="underline">excell'd</hi>, was never found,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-14"> The Man <hi rend="underline">above</hi> or <hi rend="underline">under</hi> Ground.</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-15"> This M<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">ORAL</hi> is so plain to hit,</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-16"> That, had I been the G<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">OD</hi> of <hi rend="underline">Wit</hi>,</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-17"> Then in a S<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">AWPIT</hi> and wet Weather</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-393-27L7-line-18"> Shou'd Y<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">OUNG</hi> and P<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">HILIPS</hi> work together.393-27L7   </l></lg></div>
